	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=101415"><span id=" ">Rishaka</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">100 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Default [2.13]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>The damage bonus varies, and unlike bane or magic style damage, it is not added to the weapon base damage rating as far as I can tell.<br/><br/>It looks like the damage is totaled through whatever decadimentional math VI uses, then the bonus damage is added in as straight damage points.<br/><br/>So if you hit for 10 points, you end up doing 22 with the bonus damage listed.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
