	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=16401&amp;mid=103550841511066">RE: Chanter Tank!</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=16401&amp;mid=103550841511066#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Thu, Oct 24th 9:32 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=188785"><span id="Scholar">Harik</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">71 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.25]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>You are correct Rishaka<br/><br/>It is a popular misconception that damage bonus is added to a weapon's damage ratio. This is not true.<br/><br/>Let's say I was using a 10 damage 20 delay weapon. with my warrior I would probably max out around 50 damage with this (just a guess). Assuming I had a 12 damage bonus on the weapon (again, just a guess) I would do a total of 62 damage on a perfect hit.<br/><br/>Now, if this weapon was 22 damage 20 delay (adding in the damage bonus to the ratio) I would be dealing about 100 points of damage or more per hit. the change is obvious, and this is why damage bonus isn't factored into the ratio<br/><br/>Bane damage is added to the ratio as stated, damage 'bonus' is just that... an additional few bonus points of damage after the damage from the ratio has been done.<br/><br/>Hopefully that helps clear things up a bit, but since I see this so often it kinda gets on my nerves and I had to say something :) If I left anything out feel free to fill in the gaps.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Oct 24 21:14:46 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><br/><span style='color: gold;'><b>Harik</b></span style='color: gold;'><br/>16 Crusader / 15 Outfitter<br/>Antonius Bayle Server<br/><br/><span style='color: gold;'><b>Thordain</b></span style='color: gold;'> - <i>retired</i><br/>60 Paladin / 30 Warrior<br/>Ifrit Server<br/><br/>"<i>Mine name is Glenn! Cyrus's hopes and dreams... And now the Masamune... Forthwith I shall slay Magus and restore honor!</i>" - Frog<br/><br/></td></tr>
