	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=16401&amp;mid=105535030762666">RE: Chanter Tank!</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=16401&amp;mid=105535030762666#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 11th 1:32 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=156951"><span id="Scholar">Grabble</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">78 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.44]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Up till 20th level its simply:<br/><br/>(2 x Weapon Damage) + 1<br/><br/>After level 20 the damage cap dissapears and the max hit follows the easy formula:<br/><br/>(((Strength + Weapon Skill) % 100) x Weapon Damage) + Damage bonus <br/><br/>(Damage bonus is nominally 1 for those without one).<br/><br/>However... you obviously won't hit for max all the time. In practice you find its a distribution. Level difference of you and your target additionally gets dropped into this somewhere along the way... obviously if you fight green con mobs you'll find you do alot more max damage hits... and conversely if you fight red con mobs you'll hit for 1, or low damage alot more... </p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Grabble<br/>Night Elf Hunter<br/>Teranus<br/></td></tr>
